-- Conergy Develops 6.1 Megawatts of Solar Rooftop Plants in France
-- B y   S t e f a n   N i c o l a
-- 2012-01-31T10:39:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-31/conergy-develops-6-1-megawatts-of-solar-rooftop-plants-in-france.html
Conergy AG (CGYK) , a German solar-energy
company, has helped develop three power plants on rooftops in
 France .  Conergy and French solar-energy developer  Soligest 
installed more than 80,000 First Solar Inc. thin-film modules at
three rooftop plants on warehouses in Thiers, Bellene and
Montreuil with a combined capacity of 6.1 megawatts, the
Hamburg-based company said in an e-mailed statement today. The
facilities are operated by Soligest, Conergy said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stefan Nicola in Berlin at 
 snicola2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
